abstract: JPMorgan Chase said that Hewlett-Packard's Autonomy deal "sets an unfavorable precedent for future acquisitions to come."
snippet: JPMorgan Chase said that Hewlett-Packard's Autonomy deal "sets an unfavorable precedent for future acquisitions to come."
lead_paragraph: Even after Hewlett-Packard closed its $11.7 billion acquisition of Autonomy on Monday, there remains some apprehension about the price tag. H.P. paid a 64 percent premium for the British software maker.
